# Experience switcher defaults

The experience switcher exposes three controls (Concept, Platform, Theme).
**Concept and Platform must reset to a fixed default on every page refresh,
no matter what the shopper picked in the previous session.**

| Control | Default | Persistence |
|---|---|---|
| Concept switcher (`mode`) | `"immersive"` | None — refresh always resets |
| Platform switcher (`viewportMode`) | `"desktop"` | None — refresh always resets |
| Theme switcher (`theme`) | `"sf-next"` | localStorage (intentional, do NOT change) |

## Where this lives in code

The defaults are declared as **named constants** at the top of
`src/components/AgentModeBar/AgentModeContext.tsx`:

```typescript
const DEFAULT_AGENT_MODE: AgentMode = "immersive";
const DEFAULT_VIEWPORT_MODE: DemoViewportMode = "desktop";
```

Both pieces of state use plain `useState(DEFAULT_*)` — no lazy initializer
that reads from `localStorage` or `sessionStorage`, no URL-param override,
no cookie. That guarantees a clean reset on every mount.

## Forbidden patterns

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — reading localStorage at init re-introduces stale state across refreshes.
const [viewportMode, setViewportMode] = useState<DemoViewportMode>(() => {
  const saved = window.localStorage.getItem("agent-demo-viewport-mode");
  return saved === "mobile" ? "mobile" : "desktop";
});

// ❌ BAD — writing back to localStorage means the next refresh restores it.
useEffect(() => {
  window.localStorage.setItem("agent-demo-viewport-mode", viewportMode);
}, [viewportMode]);

// ✅ GOOD — hard default, no persistence.
const [viewportMode, setViewportMode] =
  useState<DemoViewportMode>(DEFAULT_VIEWPORT_MODE);
```

The `AgentModeBar` effect that mirrors `viewportMode` onto the `<html>`
element's `data-demo-viewport` attribute is fine — that's a render-time
side-effect, not persistence. It must NOT also `setItem` to localStorage.

## Why no persistence

This is a demo / prototype surface. Shoppers (and stakeholders during
demos) should always land on the canonical Immersive + Desktop story.
A previously-set Mobile or Sidecar mode would silently distort first
impressions of the build.

## Sibling rule

The refresh-time route default — every load that resolves to `/` is
rerouted to `/wingman` — lives in `refresh-defaults.mdc`. Together
they enforce that every fresh visit lands the shopper on the
immersive Wingman page in desktop mode.

## When changing this rule

1. Update the constants in `AgentModeContext.tsx`.
2. Update the table at the top of this file.
3. Search for `agent-demo-viewport-mode` and `assistant-only`
   (the previous default) to make sure no other code path was
   relying on the old behaviour.
